manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: E-ATX Computer Open Chassis Bracket Case Rack Scope of Application: Support Motherboards within 305x245mm (ATX, M‑ATX, ITX) Support Power Supply: Standard ATX Power Supply Size: Approx. 150mm / 5.9in, Approx. 86mm / 3.4in, Approx. 140-250mm / 5.5-9.8in Support: 1 SSD, 1 HDD

What motherboards and power supplies are supported by the ATX version of the motherboard? All ATX, M-ATX, ITX motherboards are supported; standard or extended ATX power supplies are supported. What motherboards are supported by the E-ATX version of the motherboard? E-ATX version can support the vast majority of E-ATX motherboards on the market, some E-ATX motherboards may appear 1-2 screw holes are not correct, can be supported by the included plastic base. Which graphics cards are supported and how many graphics cards are supported? All graphics cards can be supported, regardless of length and width; the number of graphics cards need to be based on the motherboard PCIE slot and the thickness of the graphics card, generally 3-7. Is it possible to install additional fans? The other side of the backplane can be installed with three 12cm fans (such as graphics cards longer will produce interference resulting in the inability to install); can also be used to install 120, 240, 360 water cooling row. CPU cooler height can support up to what? There is no limit to the height of CPU coolers.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This has to be one of the top ten items I have ever added to my DIY PC toolbox - it gives me a nice base to build out and test a new board, much better than the floor..... I read the reviews and I must say if you need an instruction manual to assemble these four parts you should not be building your own PC LOL

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect design, and high quality
reviews.reviewText: The case was perfect for two different motherboards: ATX and ITX-I flipped my motherboards for two projects, worked for both-Very easy to assemble, twenty minutes and everything was up and running.-Very solid and durable.-I was happy that all the mounts lined up; PSU lined up perfectly.Cons-The only thing I didn't like was cable management, would've liked it to sit 1/2 higher, but I'm going to use four leg screws and it'll be perfect.I would recommend it to anyone, and I'm quite happy w/purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Thin gauge metal... but it works.
reviews.reviewText: Seemed flimsy but I mounted it upside down on the bottom of my desk and it has not fallen yet. The screw holes were poorly threaded. Neither metric or imperial fit properly. I was able to use standard case screws but it took some force to get them installed.

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars works but directions are horrible
reviews.reviewText: mine came to me with some dents, but nothing i couldn't bend back into place. it's not meant to be pretty anyways. that said the directions are HORIBLE, use the images in this amazon product page and and just take it slow. it's pretty easy to assemble and will just fit together, so it won't take much to figure it out, but the little paper they give you will have you scratching your head. liked it enough to nab a second one.

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.5 - Documentation is very poor but product is good!
reviews.reviewText: Almost returned due to lack of documentation you may have to flip the pieces a few times to get the proper alignment, after that product very sturdy, works very well as expected. At first I didn't think any of the holes lined up but then I had to turn it around and flip it upside-down XD. Maybe I'm just slow but the manual or leaf-let didnt help -- Use the product pictures on the amazon store!I have an ATX board on it with an ATX PSU. So far so good, happy for the purchase, the triangle supports really help and my hardware feels secure in the case. I have mine vertically sitting on the table (as in the picture) but will move it to be horizontal when I put it where my old other PC was.Good for bench and test machines, but keep in mind there are no rubber feet on the bottom so be careful not to scratch whatever surface you put it on. I'm sure some could easily be added.
